{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. In a disposable repository, add an activated `code_review` entry for\n   `project.review-phase-boundaries` to `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` with\n   `exec: \"AGENT\"`, `block_threshold: 0.90`, and `blocking_enabled: false`.\n2. Add the matching project prompt and eval spec under `.rebar/prompts/` and\n   `.rebar/evals/`.\n3. Run the four-pass code-review workflow over a matching prompt/reviewer diff, then run the\n   per-criterion eval command for the activated project criterion.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n\n**Expected:** the activated project criterion is resolved from the reviewed repository, runs\nexactly once in Pass 1, carries its logical `project.*` criterion id into findings, is judged by\nPass 3 using the repository's effective routing, and can be evaluated through the existing\nper-criterion eval surface.\n\n**Actual:** `gates/code-review.yaml` contains only a static built-in prompt list;\n`CodeReviewBatchRunner` iterates only that list; `code_review_decide` calls\n`registry.threshold_for` and `nit_suppressed_criteria` without the repository's effective routing;\nand `eval_solver._code_review_prompt_id` accepts only the base, verifier, and packaged overlay ids.\nThe overlay vocabulary therefore advertises net-new code-review project criteria that cannot run or\ncontrol their configured posture end to end.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nADR 0017 completed the shared overlay merge and exposed `code_review.effective_criteria` /\n`effective_routing`, but code review never received the runner-side dynamic fan-in that plan review\nuses, nor repo-aware Pass-3 lookup or project-id eval resolution. This is a generic integration gap,\nnot a special case for the boundary criterion.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Add `CODE_REVIEW_PROMPT_PREFIX = \"code-review-\"` and a gate-keyed\n  `criterion_prompt_id(criterion_id, *, gate_key=\"plan_review\")`; the default preserves existing\n  plan-review callers while code-review `project.<name>` maps to\n  `code-review-project-<name-with-dots-replaced-by-dashes>`.\n- Fan activated non-DET code-review project criteria into `round_a` only. The one\n  `CodeReviewBatchRunner` shared across `round_a` and `round_b` deduplicates physical ids against\n  static criteria and records fan-in completion, so `round_b` cannot run them again. Do not change\n  the version-pinned workflow schema or hard-code project ids in packaged YAML.\n- Resolve project prompts from the reviewed snapshot; a missing or malformed activated prompt\n  fails loudly as a located configuration error rather than being silently skipped.\n- Bind Pass 3 threshold and nit-suppression lookup to `effective_routing(ctx.repo_root)`.\n- Extend the existing criterion-eval resolver to recognize activated code-review project criteria\n  and load their `.rebar/evals/<prompt-id>.eval.yaml` specs. The resolver reuses\n  `_run_code_review_case`, reads each case's `diff` key, and returns the prompt's native findings;\n  it does not route project code-review criteria through plan-review `pass1_chunk` or add a new arm.\n- Extend the `criteria eval` CLI preflight to accept a logical code-review project id only when it\n  appears in `code_review.effective_criteria(repo_root)`. Compare membership in plan-review and\n  code-review registries: no match is unknown, exactly one selects that gate, and a dual-gate match\n  is an explicit ambiguity error. Pass the selected gate through `calibrate_criterion` to the\n  gate-keyed prompt mapper; unknown, inactive, and ambiguous ids remain errors.\n- Preserve byte-for-byte behavior for repositories without a code-review project overlay.\n\nOut of scope: authoring `project.review-phase-boundaries`, changing the four-pass decision math,\nchanging packaged built-in criteria, or deploying a Gerrit dogfood criterion.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nLikely seams are `src/rebar/llm/criteria/ids.py`,\n`src/rebar/llm/code_review/batch_runner.py`,\n`src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py`, and\n`src/rebar/llm/evals/eval_solver.py`, `src/rebar/llm/evals/eval.py`, plus the CLI preflight in\n`src/rebar/_cli/_llm_eval_commands.py`. Reuse the existing plan-review runner-side fan-in pattern;\ndo not add a project-specific branch or a new workflow DSL field. Eval recognition must invert the\nsame sanitized mapping and confirm the logical id is active in the repository-effective registry;\na prefix match alone is insufficient. `_code_review_prompt_id` therefore receives `repo_root`,\nbuilds an active logical-to-physical map with `criterion_prompt_id(..., gate_key=\"code_review\")`,\nand returns the input physical id only when it is one of those computed values. This avoids parsing\nthe forward-only filename back into a logical id.\n\nIn `code_review_decide`, compute `routing = registry.effective_routing(ctx.repo_root)` once, pass a\ncallback using that map to `pass3_over_findings`, and pass the same map to\n`nit_suppressed_criteria`. Both threshold/posture and nit suppression must be repo-aware together.\nThe authoring preview/editor remain plan-review-only and use the mapper's default; adding a visual\ncode-review criterion editor is out of scope.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] An offline full-gate test activates a synthetic code-review `project.*` criterion and proves\n  its project prompt runs once across same-runner `round_a` and `round_b` requests; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k fan_in`.\n- [ ] A finding tagged only with the synthetic project id records the overlay's configured\n  `block_threshold` and `blocking_enabled` values in Pass 3, and overlay `nit_suppressed` overrides\n  are honored; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k routing`.\n- [ ] An activated project criterion with a missing or malformed prompt fails with a located error,\n  while an overlay-absent repository produces the pre-change workflow result; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k 'missing or parity'`.\n- [ ] The criterion eval resolver accepts an activated code-review project id and its sanitized\n  prompt id, the CLI preflight admits the logical id, the repository eval spec loads, and unknown or\n  inactive ids are rejected. Its `diff` fixture runs through `_run_code_review_case` and produces\n  native findings without entering the plan-review criterion arm; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_code_review_project_criteria.py -k 'eval or cli'`.\n- [ ] Existing shared-overlay and four-pass code-review regression suites remain green; verify with\n  `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_unified_criteria.py tests/unit/test_code_review_evals.py\n  tests/unit/workflow/test_code_review_workflow.py`.\n\n## Rollback\n\nRevert the additive fan-in, repo-aware lookup, and eval-resolution changes together. Repositories\nwithout a project code-review overlay remain the compatibility baseline, so rollback requires no\ndata migration or cleanup."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784320460490375001,"uuid":"0251e828-815f-4acb-b27f-057502c2bdab"}